WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:04.709
-Here are your morning
announcements.

00:04.750 --> 00:07.500
I'd like to remind my student
council that we have a meeting
after school.

00:07.542 --> 00:10.667
We'd also like to congratulate
the girls softball team.

00:10.709 --> 00:13.166
Who took down St. Pat's, 2-0.

00:13.208 --> 00:17.417
[Auditorium claps]

00:17.458 --> 00:21.125
-Next Wednesday the chess club
will be meeting in Ms. Amra's
class...

00:21.166 --> 00:23.834
-[Maya mouths]: Sorry.
-...As the cafeteria will
be closed after school.

00:23.875 --> 00:26.959
-[Quietly]: So, how did it go?
-[Quietly]: Good...
-[Natalie]:Students and staff...

00:27.000 --> 00:29.333
to attend the annual Xavier
Academy spelling bee...
-And bad.

00:29.375 --> 00:31.291
-[Natalie]: This Thursday
afternoon in the auditorium...

00:31.333 --> 00:33.500
-I want details.
-Oh god.

00:33.542 --> 00:36.291
-[Quietly]: Hey, Stephan,
give me your seat.
-[Announcements continue]

00:36.333 --> 00:38.709
-Why?
-Don't ask why, just do what
you're told. Thank you. Bye bye.

00:38.750 --> 00:41.667
-[Announcements continue]
-Hey Stephan.

00:41.709 --> 00:44.500
-[Gerry whispers]: Oh boy.
-You're not looking too
good Mr. D.

00:44.542 --> 00:46.750
-Not now Jimmy.
-Oh hey, that's a nice shiner
man.

00:46.792 --> 00:50.333
-You should see the other guys.
-[Natalie]: Benjamin Ackerman
recently took home first prize..

00:50.375 --> 00:53.000
-There's like, six of them okay?
-Oh I bet.
-So, one guy got a shot at me.

00:53.041 --> 00:55.250
-[Natalie]: At the Highland
Music Competition.
-Oh yeah?

00:55.291 --> 00:57.250
-Yeah, you're lucky you weren't
there. Grasscutter.

00:57.291 --> 01:01.166
[Applause]

01:01.208 --> 01:04.291
[♪ Bagpipes warm up]
-Oh my god.

01:04.333 --> 01:07.291
[♪ Bagpipes warm up]

01:07.333 --> 01:09.667
[♪ Scotland the brave
on Bagpipes]

01:09.709 --> 01:13.000
[♪ Scotland the brave
on Bagpipes]

01:13.041 --> 01:16.291
[♪ Scotland the brave
on Bagpipes]

01:16.333 --> 01:19.291
[♪ Scotland the brave
on Bagpipes]

01:19.333 --> 01:22.083
[♪ Scotland the brave
on Bagpipes]

01:22.125 --> 01:25.250
[♪ Scotland the Brave, Bagpipes]
-Okay, what happened
after I left?

01:25.291 --> 01:28.166
♪ I'm awesome, no you're
not dude don't lie ♪

01:28.208 --> 01:30.542
♪ I'm awesome, I'm driving
around in my mom's ride ♪

01:30.583 --> 01:33.208
♪ I'm awesome, a quarter
of my life gone by ♪

01:34.250 --> 01:36.542
♪ I'm awesome ♪

01:37.959 --> 01:40.375
[♪ Dance Music]
[Sound of glass clinking]

01:40.417 --> 01:43.583
-Everyone, I'd like to raise
a glass to you all.

01:43.625 --> 01:46.041
In recognition of all
your hard work.

01:46.083 --> 01:48.417
The school can be like
a rudderless ship without...

01:48.458 --> 01:51.959
The efforts and dedication
of a hard working crew.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.333
Here's to all of you.
Thank you.

01:54.375 --> 01:56.750
-Teachers everywhere!

01:56.792 --> 01:59.250
-And...Um...

02:00.417 --> 02:02.750
You know when I think of our
little rag tag gang...

02:02.792 --> 02:05.000
Which I often do.

02:05.041 --> 02:07.250
I like to think of
it as a family.

02:07.291 --> 02:11.041
And much like a family you
don't have to like the members
of your family, but...

02:11.083 --> 02:13.333
But you do have to love them.
-Robert.

02:13.375 --> 02:15.375
-And if I'm being honest...
-Robert, sit down.

02:15.417 --> 02:17.583
-[Robert]: Yup.
-Sir, is this open bar for us?

02:17.625 --> 02:19.834
-No.
-Why would it be?

02:19.875 --> 02:22.208
-You know what we should do?
Let's play the compliment game.

02:22.250 --> 02:24.250
-I gotta go.
-No, no, no it's fun.

02:24.291 --> 02:27.083
Okay, I don't have anything
nice to say about you anyway.

02:27.125 --> 02:29.625
Here's how it works. We'll go
counter clockwise, I'll start
with you.

02:29.667 --> 02:31.834
I pay a compliment and you
can pay it forward

02:31.875 --> 02:34.083
or pay it backward whatever
you like.

02:34.125 --> 02:36.458
The word father, in
the dictionary...
-I'll be back.

02:36.500 --> 02:40.291
-Okay, I'll get him later.
Um...Lisa!

02:40.333 --> 02:43.250
You're in my compliment scope.
-Skipped one.

02:43.291 --> 02:47.250
-You are easily the most
consistently...

02:48.667 --> 02:54.917
Organized, and I continue
to be amazed. And you're clean.

02:54.959 --> 02:57.250
-Awww.
-[Robert]: Cheers.

02:57.291 --> 02:59.750
-Thank you Robert.
-So, um, your turn.

02:59.792 --> 03:02.083
-Huh?
-Go.

03:02.125 --> 03:06.375
-Simon, do you...? You probably
have something nice to say to
Robert, hey?

03:06.417 --> 03:08.417
-Don't overthink it,
just say something.

03:08.458 --> 03:11.959
-Ahhhhhhhhh...yeah...

03:14.375 --> 03:16.375
-[Gerry quietly]: Boy oh boy.
-How's the teacher party?

03:16.417 --> 03:20.291
-Lame. I have to stay though,
because Callaghan arranged it.

03:20.333 --> 03:23.000
Once he leaves, I leave.
-Give it a couple hours man.

03:23.041 --> 03:25.875
Alcohol plus time, it's an
equation that always equals fun.

03:25.917 --> 03:28.125
-There's no fun to be
had tonight with them.

03:28.166 --> 03:30.375
-They can't all be wild
like you.
-True.

03:30.417 --> 03:32.417
-Is that kiwi watermelon?
Want me to get you another one?

03:32.458 --> 03:34.709
-Why? It's half full.
Trying to get me wasted?

03:35.834 --> 03:38.041
-Wow! Sir.

03:38.083 --> 03:41.250
-I did not realize your life
outside of work was so
interesting.

03:41.291 --> 03:43.375
-You know, just 'cause you work
here now, Jimmy, doesn't mean

03:43.417 --> 03:45.875
you can talk to me when I'm
here. So, stay away from me.

03:45.917 --> 03:48.208
-That's rude.
-I gotta clean this section sir.

03:48.250 --> 03:50.500
-[Gerry]: Oh, excuse me.
-Jimmy's incredibly thorough.

03:50.542 --> 03:52.750
-Thank you. You know, you travel
with a pretty crazy crowd.

03:52.792 --> 03:55.959
What's the after party? Busting
out the backgammon table?

03:56.000 --> 03:59.667
-I'm only here because I have
to be. That is my crowd.

03:59.709 --> 04:02.083
Look at that, right there.

04:02.125 --> 04:04.375
In a normal situation, I'd be
sitting with them.

04:04.417 --> 04:06.333
Because beautiful people
hang out with beautiful people.

04:08.041 --> 04:10.667
That girl, see that girl
with the short hair?
-[Bill and Jimmy]: Mmm hmm.

04:10.709 --> 04:13.792
-[Gerry]: That's my girl. And at
the end of the night, you know
what would happen?

04:13.834 --> 04:16.250
I'd go home with that group
of people and we'd party
some more.

04:16.291 --> 04:20.500
Probably skinny dip with
some cops, some watermelons.

04:20.542 --> 04:23.417
That's what's gonna happen...
With that girl.

04:23.458 --> 04:26.250
-Her? Yeah right, she
would never talk to you.

04:26.291 --> 04:28.542
-[Laughs]: She would never
talk...

04:28.583 --> 04:31.500
-I mean, if she were your
therapist then she'd have
to talk to you...

04:31.542 --> 04:35.583
-[Bill laughs]
-By law. But, ah, besides that,
no I don't see it happening.

04:35.625 --> 04:38.250
-Suddenly you're a funny guy.
Can't spell cat and you're 21.

04:38.291 --> 04:43.542
I'll show you both, how I can
talk to that girl and you can
learn something little boy.

04:46.083 --> 04:49.750
Another one of these, I gotta
get a little tipsy before I go.

04:49.792 --> 04:52.500
-Now I get it, that's good.
[Laughs]

04:52.542 --> 04:54.458
-Brrr.
[Laughs]

04:54.500 --> 04:56.709
-I really like your dress Bobbi.
-What?!

04:56.750 --> 04:59.041
Oh this is just a
ra, ra, ra, ra.

04:59.083 --> 05:01.750
-[Dwyer laughs]: What I meant
was, you clean up real nice.

05:01.792 --> 05:04.750
-Oh, that's...You are...
You're clean.

05:04.792 --> 05:07.583
You're nice, you're a clean guy.
-Ow!

05:07.625 --> 05:09.834
-Sorry.
-Did you just kick me?

05:09.875 --> 05:13.250
-Yeah, but it was just like
a playful tap, like a love tap.

05:14.583 --> 05:16.542
I'm so sorry.

05:17.500 --> 05:19.792
Oh, I know what you're
going to say.

05:19.834 --> 05:23.083
[Laughs]: Do ya?
Because I'm speechless.

05:23.125 --> 05:25.709
-He's just so pretty, you know?
Makes me nervous.

05:25.750 --> 05:28.083
-Well, I heard that his
marriage is over.

05:28.125 --> 05:30.625
-Hello.
-So...

05:30.667 --> 05:34.125
Keep kicking.
Haha. Cheers!

05:36.208 --> 05:38.792
-Yoga instructor.
-Excuse me?

05:38.834 --> 05:41.417
-You teach yoga.
-[Laughs]: Not exactly.

05:41.458 --> 05:43.625
-Really? I'm usually bang on
with that.

05:43.667 --> 05:46.291
-It's a useful skill to have.
-It's a skill alright.

05:46.333 --> 05:49.834
-That guy there, a sous chef.
French for under chef.

05:49.875 --> 05:52.542
No, I don't know what he does.
-Wow. [Laughs]

05:52.583 --> 05:54.542
-You are funny.
-Oh, thank you.

05:54.583 --> 05:57.834
-Here's your bill.
-Oh, ah...

05:57.875 --> 06:00.208
I got that.
-Seriously?

06:00.250 --> 06:02.500
-Do I look like I'm joking?
-That's very generous of you.

06:02.542 --> 06:07.333
-You can be generous when
you make 51 thousand dollars
a year.

06:07.375 --> 06:11.500
-Sorry?
-Fifty one G's come
into my house.

06:11.542 --> 06:14.709
-Well, I have a roommate, but...
-Is that...net?

06:14.750 --> 06:18.625
-[Laughs]: Net, it's gross.

06:18.667 --> 06:21.125
-Right, thank you for that.
-You're welcome.

06:21.166 --> 06:23.375
-I will be getting back
to my friends.
-No problem.

06:23.417 --> 06:26.917
-Whoa! haha. You sneaky devil.

06:28.041 --> 06:32.208
I'm not getting the whole table.
245 dollars?

06:32.250 --> 06:36.250
Renege. I'll give you 42 dollars
for your portion.

06:36.291 --> 06:38.917
-No, that's fine.
-Good to meet you.

06:38.959 --> 06:41.166
-Smooth.
-Thank you.

06:41.959 --> 06:45.709
-Ooh, where's lover man?
-Dwyer?

06:45.750 --> 06:47.959
No, he said he was tired.
He was going to go home.

06:48.000 --> 06:50.834
-Well then, why aren't you going
with him? Come on, get in there.

06:50.875 --> 06:54.458
-I tried. He's just not picking
up what I'm throwing down.

06:54.500 --> 06:56.500
-How would he?
-May I join you fine ladies?

06:56.542 --> 06:59.417
-[Bobbi and Trudy]: No.
-Enchanté

06:59.458 --> 07:02.583
-Cheers.
-I should do that with you.
-Mmm mmm.

07:04.792 --> 07:08.041
-Oohhh, Jimmy the chick magnet.

07:08.083 --> 07:12.542
I get it. Tight sleeves,
good hair, dreamy eyes.

07:12.583 --> 07:16.834
Sink into those eyes. [Laughs]
Oh to be Jimmy for a day.

07:16.875 --> 07:20.291
-First of all, he wouldn't even
have met her if it wasn't for
me.

07:20.333 --> 07:23.542
-Oh yeah?
-Yeah, I softened her up.
Now he's cutting my grass.

07:23.583 --> 07:28.417
-Your heat melted the icy
exterior and now Jimmy's
enjoying the chewy centre.

07:28.458 --> 07:31.834
[Clucks mouth]
-What are you talking about?

07:31.875 --> 07:35.750
He's never going to get her.
She's a woman, he's a boy.

07:35.792 --> 07:39.625
-Still, poor form Jimmy.
Poor form.

07:39.667 --> 07:42.542
-No, I'm going to get her back.

07:42.583 --> 07:47.250
-You know what? The Gerry
I know would never take things
lying down.

07:47.291 --> 07:49.542
-Thanks buddy.
-Gerry Smithers.

07:49.583 --> 07:52.417
-Oh.
-I went to sleep away camp
with him. He was a bulldog.

07:52.458 --> 07:54.959
-[Gerry]: Okay.
-He used to get in arguments
every day with the staff.

07:55.000 --> 07:57.500
-[Gerry]: Alright.
-He got kicked out on the
second day of camp.

07:57.542 --> 08:00.583
-That's a great story Simon.
-You could really take a page
out of that Gerry's book.

08:00.625 --> 08:02.625
-I won't.

08:02.667 --> 08:05.625
-'Cause the other Gerry I know
has a heart of gold once you get
to know him.

08:05.667 --> 08:07.625
-Stop it.
-Gerry White.

08:07.667 --> 08:10.792
He was a high school friend.
Deaf mute...
-Simon this is...

08:10.834 --> 08:13.458
-But if you had read some of the
things he wrote. Oh my goodness.

08:13.500 --> 08:15.667
-Okay.
-He was a poet.

08:15.709 --> 08:17.667
-Can I just be alone right now?
For a second.

08:17.709 --> 08:20.667
-Stay strong. You know,
there's third Gerry I know.

08:20.709 --> 08:24.417
-Why wouldn't there be
a third Gerry?
-And that Gerry, never gives up.

08:24.458 --> 08:26.667
-Right, what's that Gerry's
last name?

08:26.709 --> 08:29.709
-D.
-That's not a last name.

08:29.750 --> 08:31.709
-It's you.

08:31.750 --> 08:34.333
-I'm not...my last name's not D,
it's Duncan.

08:34.375 --> 08:37.542
-What?
-Yeah, the kids call me Mr. D,
but it stands for Duncan.

08:37.583 --> 08:39.792
Gerry Duncan's my name.
-Since when?

08:39.834 --> 08:41.834
-What are? Are you kidding me?
-Good Lord.

08:41.875 --> 08:44.083
-What do you think I'm D period?
-Duncan?

08:44.125 --> 08:46.417
-Just go. You're not helping.
-Holy macaroni. Duncan?

08:46.458 --> 08:48.667
-Get out of here.
-No, I don't like that.

08:48.709 --> 08:50.750
-Alright.
-Oh, I gotta reassess things.

08:50.792 --> 08:52.959
-Okay, what are you doing? Get
away, why'd you come here?

08:53.000 --> 08:55.417
-D? Meh, I don't even remember.

08:57.542 --> 09:00.500
-[Maya]: Thanks again, Ms.
Mason, for letting me shadow you
for the next few weeks.

09:00.542 --> 09:03.500
-I also volunteered at a school
when I started studying
education.

09:03.542 --> 09:05.834
-We, here's to teaching.
Gin and Tonic?

09:05.875 --> 09:10.041
-Oh, no thank you. I'm going
to stick with my soda water
tonight.

09:10.083 --> 09:12.333
-That's no fun.

09:12.375 --> 09:14.583
[♪ Dance Music plays in the bar]

09:14.625 --> 09:17.959
-You know, he's a bus boy right?
-Excuse me?

09:18.000 --> 09:21.542
-He probably makes about
20 thousand dollars a year.

09:21.583 --> 09:25.834
Maybe, tops.
-We were actually in the middle
of having a conversation.

09:25.875 --> 09:28.834
-Yeah, come on Mr. D.
-Don't call me that here.

09:28.875 --> 09:32.458
-Okay, you know what? Why don't
you go hang out with, I dunno,
Mr. Cheeley over there.

09:32.500 --> 09:34.667
-Yeah, yeah.
-He seems like your speed.

09:34.709 --> 09:36.959
-No, I think I'll hang out here
because...
[♪ Music gets louder]

09:37.000 --> 09:39.250
-Simon, come here!
Quick, quick, quick.

09:39.291 --> 09:42.208
Hold the chair, hold the chair.
[♪ Shake you down by
Gregory Abbott is playing]

09:42.250 --> 09:44.625
-You hold this chair okay?
Now you stay there.

09:44.667 --> 09:47.709
No, no you stay there. No,
don't come up. I need you to
stay there and do the back up.

09:47.750 --> 09:50.208
[Lip synching]: Yeah.

09:50.250 --> 09:54.959
[♪ Music]

09:55.000 --> 09:59.417
[Lip synching]: Girl I've been
watching you

09:59.458 --> 10:01.875
[♪ Music]

10:01.917 --> 10:06.208
[Lip synching]: from so far
across the floor now baby

10:06.250 --> 10:10.834
[Lip synching]:
that's nothing new

10:10.875 --> 10:16.709
I've watched you
so many times before now baby

10:16.750 --> 10:19.500
I see that look in your eyes

10:19.542 --> 10:22.125
-[Lip synching]: Look in your
eyes.

10:22.166 --> 10:24.750
-[Lip synching]:
and what it's telling me

10:24.792 --> 10:30.333
-[Lip synching]: and you know
oh girl that I'm not shy

10:30.375 --> 10:32.917
-[Lip synching]:
I'm glad you picked up

10:32.959 --> 10:36.834
-[Lip synching]:
On my telepathy now baby

10:36.875 --> 10:39.000
-[Lip synching]:
You read my mind you know

10:39.041 --> 10:42.417
-[Lip synching]: Girl I wanna
shake you down well, well

10:42.458 --> 10:46.208
-[Lip synching]: I can give you
all the loving you need

10:46.250 --> 10:48.500
-[Lip synching]: I'm gonna
love you

10:48.542 --> 10:52.417
-[Lip synching]: Come on let
me take you down oh baby.

10:52.458 --> 10:56.000
-[Song continues]: ♪ We'll go
all the way to heaven ♪

10:56.041 --> 10:58.333
-[Song continues]: ♪ Oh! I've
been missing you ♪

10:58.375 --> 11:01.000
-Hey! Get off the bar!

11:01.041 --> 11:03.333
Give me that.

11:03.375 --> 11:07.333
-[Song continues]: ♪ And the way
you make me feel inside ♪
-[People cheer]

11:07.375 --> 11:09.709
-There you go.
-[Song continues]:
♪ What can I do ♪

11:09.750 --> 11:12.083
-That go how you wanted?
-I thought I had her.

11:12.125 --> 11:14.750
-Come on.
-You screwed it up buddy,
you were off.

11:14.792 --> 11:17.291
-No.
-That's why! No, you were off.
That's what did it.

11:17.333 --> 11:20.333
Don't push me Bill.
Dammit.

11:20.375 --> 11:22.792
-Scooch in.
-No, no, no.

11:22.834 --> 11:24.792
-Oh scooch in.
-I'm going to get going.

11:24.834 --> 11:27.542
-No, I think you might want
to hang around a little bit.

11:27.583 --> 11:29.750
-No, I've had enough
and I want to go home.

11:29.792 --> 11:31.792
-The night is young Bobbi.
-[Bobbi sighs]

11:31.834 --> 11:34.750
-And I took care of it.
-What?

11:34.792 --> 11:38.083
-I laid the groundwork.
-[Both giggle]

11:38.125 --> 11:41.750
-Okay, what kind of groundwork?
-He's ripe for the pickin'.

11:41.792 --> 11:44.000
-English, I don't know
what you're saying.

11:44.041 --> 11:46.083
-Oh, Paul.
-Mmm hmm.

11:46.125 --> 11:48.792
-I gave him a little something
and he won't be going anywhere
anytime soon.

11:48.834 --> 11:51.625
-Oh my god, you drugged him?
-No, I did not.

11:51.667 --> 11:54.000
-Okay.
-I just gave him a few
Jagerbombs.

11:54.041 --> 11:58.166
-HI!
-[Trudy and Bobbi laugh]

11:58.208 --> 12:00.375
-You're welcome.

12:00.417 --> 12:02.875
-Well Maya, this is a
work event.

12:02.917 --> 12:05.875
And, you'll learn when
you become a teacher...

12:05.917 --> 12:08.834
That you can go out with
colleagues so long as you
keep it professional.

12:08.875 --> 12:10.875
-What's the worst
that can happen?

12:10.917 --> 12:13.917
-Sometimes, when people drink,
they say and do things they
regret.

12:13.959 --> 12:16.875
-Come on, let your hair down.
Don't be so boring.

12:16.917 --> 12:19.834
-Do you think I'm boring?
Is that what the students are
saying?

12:19.875 --> 12:23.959
Do you know how exhausting
it can be...

12:24.000 --> 12:27.083
To always be the responsible
one every single day?

12:27.125 --> 12:29.542
Do you know how tiring that is?

12:29.583 --> 12:33.333
-Alright ladies, I'm outta here.
Have fun, not too much fun.

12:33.375 --> 12:36.500
What am I saying? You.
[Laughs]

12:36.542 --> 12:38.750
I'll see you tomorrow.

12:39.875 --> 12:41.834
-Screw this.

12:41.875 --> 12:44.583
-[♪ Dance music in background]

12:44.625 --> 12:46.917
[♪ Dance music in background]

12:46.959 --> 12:49.917
[♪ Dance music in background]
-[Lisa exhales]

12:49.959 --> 12:53.667
-[♪ Dance music in background]

12:53.709 --> 12:56.041
-[Exhales]: Oh that's better.

12:56.083 --> 12:58.458
-Don't feel bad buddy.
We all lose it eventually.

12:58.500 --> 13:01.208
-I haven't lost it.
-That's a good point.

13:01.250 --> 13:04.041
Can't really lose something
you never had.
-[Quietly]: Oh my god.

13:04.083 --> 13:07.291
-Is this seat taken?
-No, it's all yours.

13:07.333 --> 13:08.834
-Emma.
-Oh, Gerry. Hi.

13:10.000 --> 13:12.834
-Well, that was a great
performance earlier Gerry.

13:12.875 --> 13:16.709
I love that song.
-Oh, me too. Thank you Emma.

13:16.750 --> 13:19.542
-You know, my friend and I
were saying that you've got
some great moves too.

13:19.583 --> 13:23.542
-Ahhh. So someone did notice.
Thank you.

13:23.583 --> 13:27.709
-You've got really open hips.
-Yeah.

13:27.750 --> 13:32.000
-Did you ever train in ballet?
-No, I stretch.

13:32.041 --> 13:34.667
A lot.
-Well, it shows.

13:35.458 --> 13:38.166
-Do you want a drink Emma?
-Ohh.

13:38.208 --> 13:41.959
-Two banana raspberry's.
-Me and my friend were
just leaving.

13:42.000 --> 13:45.500
-Ah, too bad for me.
-But say, why don't you join us.

13:46.834 --> 13:48.917
You know, see where
the night takes us.

13:51.917 --> 13:55.041
-You mean...?
I...

13:56.792 --> 13:59.125
[Whispers]: Should I
go for a threesome?

13:59.166 --> 14:01.667
-[Mouths]: Do it.
-It would be fun right?

14:03.959 --> 14:06.959
-Yes.
Are you listening to this?

14:07.000 --> 14:09.000
-I am.
-[Laughs]: Whoo!

14:09.041 --> 14:11.500
You got me excited.
Oh man.

14:11.542 --> 14:14.291
No drinks, 'cause I'm leaving
with Emma and her friend.

14:14.333 --> 14:16.917
-You sure you can handle that?
-Can I handle it?

14:16.959 --> 14:20.792
You think I can handle it? Yeah!
Apparently Emma and her friend
think I can handle it.

14:20.834 --> 14:23.041
-[Emma]: He's into it.

14:23.083 --> 14:25.709
[Gerry]: I am def...
-[Emma]: Gerry this is my
husband, Ted.

14:25.750 --> 14:28.000
-[Bill laughs]
-Hello.

14:30.542 --> 14:33.208
-You already said yes.

14:33.250 --> 14:37.375
-Who refers to their husband
as their friend in a...

14:37.417 --> 14:40.959
-Well of course he's my friend.
He's my best friend.

14:41.000 --> 14:43.166
We wouldn't have got married
otherwise.

14:43.208 --> 14:46.125
-Is there a problem?
-There's a problem.

14:46.166 --> 14:50.375
You tricked me. You tricked me.
And I don't have to follow
through 'cause I said yes.

14:50.417 --> 14:53.000
Alright? But no one uses
the word friend...

14:53.041 --> 14:59.625
In that way and then substitutes
a burly looking husband.

14:59.667 --> 15:03.166
Sorry.
-So, are you coming or...?

15:03.208 --> 15:07.125
-No! I'm not coming.
[Whispers]: Weirdo.

15:07.166 --> 15:09.166
-Alright, let's go.

15:10.125 --> 15:12.166
-Well, it was very nice
to meet you anyways.

15:12.208 --> 15:14.583
-Yeah, nice to meet you too.

15:16.166 --> 15:18.083
Weirdo!
-I think you ruined their night.

15:18.125 --> 15:21.000
-[Dwyer]: Hey hey!
-Oh here he comes...get...
don't come over here.

15:21.041 --> 15:23.917
Oh no, please Paul.
Don't come near me.

15:23.959 --> 15:26.125
Don't come near me.
Don't come near me.

15:26.166 --> 15:28.709
-Whoo!
-[Bill]: Mmm hmm.

15:28.750 --> 15:30.959
-[Dwyer laughs]
-Oh gosh, Paul.

15:31.000 --> 15:33.917
Please stop. Get your
hands off me.
-Whoo!

15:33.959 --> 15:36.166
Stop? Can you stop?

15:37.291 --> 15:40.375
[♪ Dance Music]

15:40.417 --> 15:43.208
-Did you just see what happened?
-Mmmmmm.

15:43.250 --> 15:46.709
Jimmy leaving with your chewy
core. Yeah, he's unstoppable.

15:46.750 --> 15:49.834
-No, I just got propositioned
by a woman.

15:49.875 --> 15:52.083
-Nooo!
-For a threesome.

15:52.125 --> 15:54.083
-No way!
-Yes way!

15:54.125 --> 15:56.375
-Ohh.
-Two guys one girl. Just sayin'.

15:56.417 --> 15:59.208
-It's still a threesome right?
-What's going on? Why are
you still here?

15:59.250 --> 16:01.208
-I'm not gonna go home
with a girl and a guy.

16:01.250 --> 16:03.792
Sends quite a message to Jimmy,
you make sure you tell him.

16:03.834 --> 16:06.000
-Yeah, I'll let him know.
-Absolutely.

16:06.041 --> 16:08.166
Which message?
-That I'm a man, he's a boy.

16:08.208 --> 16:10.750
That I'm not passed my
prime. He knows that.

16:10.792 --> 16:13.041
-Yeah, no, I don't think he's
going to get that.

16:13.083 --> 16:15.917
-Who does he think he is?
With his young buck attitude
and his strong physique?

16:15.959 --> 16:18.166
-I'm strong.
-Very strong.

16:18.208 --> 16:20.625
-Jimmy's probably a bit
stronger but you're a
strong man, for sure.

16:20.667 --> 16:23.959
-Haha, oh right. I'm stronger
than Jimmy. I'm stronger than
you and I'm stronger than you.

16:24.000 --> 16:26.458
-Alright, let's see how strong
you are Gerry.
-You wanna arm wrestle?

16:26.500 --> 16:28.709
-Nope, put your arm
just like this.
-Okay, like that?

16:28.750 --> 16:31.083
-I'm gonna pull your fist down.
-You're gonna what?
-[Bill]: Gerry.

16:31.125 --> 16:33.291
-I'm gonna pull your fist down.
-You're gonna pull...?

16:33.333 --> 16:36.083
-Wanna give this some thought?
-[Simon]: Bill. Shut your mouth
please.

16:36.125 --> 16:38.291
-Would you shut up? Just let me
show him how strong I am.

16:38.333 --> 16:40.291
You're not gonna pull my fist
down. With those weak arms?

16:40.333 --> 16:42.750
-[Simon]: Oh!
-Okay, let's go.
-[Bill]: Gerry pull really hard.

16:42.792 --> 16:45.166
-Yeah, I know what to do.
-[Bill]: Show him how man
you are.

16:45.208 --> 16:47.667
-I know what to do.
Yeah, that's good.
-[Bill]: Pull hard. Be a man.

16:47.709 --> 16:50.166
-[Simon grunts]: Gerry.
-Nothing there Simon.

16:50.208 --> 16:52.458
-[Simon yells]: And bang-a-rang.
-[Gerry grunts in pain]

16:52.500 --> 16:55.542
-[Simon and Bill laugh]
-[Gerry]: Oh come on.

16:55.583 --> 16:58.583
Why'd you do that?
Oh god, that...
-Come on Gerry, that's...

16:58.625 --> 17:01.166
-That's pretty funny.
-That's a stupid game!
Why would you do that?

17:01.208 --> 17:03.291
-I can't believe you didn't
know that.
-[Gerry]: Oh!

17:03.333 --> 17:05.375
-[Bill and Simon]: Oh!
-How's that idiot?

17:09.834 --> 17:13.542
-[Trudy laughs]
[Claps]

17:13.583 --> 17:16.458
Bravo Galka.
[Laughing]: Bravo.

17:17.500 --> 17:19.500
Slut.

17:21.000 --> 17:23.417
[Bobbi's out of breath]

17:24.583 --> 17:27.125
[Laughs a bit]

17:27.166 --> 17:29.417
[Laughs a bit]

17:30.291 --> 17:32.333
-[Robert is out of breath]:

17:32.375 --> 17:35.208
M'lady. Your grape stompers.

17:35.250 --> 17:39.417
-Yup. Let's just not talk about
this ever again, okay Robert?

17:39.458 --> 17:41.834
-On the DL.
-Yeah.

17:41.875 --> 17:44.041
-Gotcha.

17:49.667 --> 17:51.834
-[Clears throat]: Just gonna
walk this off.

17:51.875 --> 17:54.792
-[♪ Bagpipes,
Scotland the Brave]

17:54.834 --> 17:58.667
-[♪ Bagpipes,
Scotland the Brave]

17:58.709 --> 18:03.250
-[Auditorium claps]

18:03.291 --> 18:05.667
-Thank you Benjamin.
Thank you Natalie.

18:05.709 --> 18:08.208
Before we wrap up today's
assembly, I just want to take

18:08.250 --> 18:13.417
this opportunity to introduce
you to Xavier Academy's new
librarian.

18:13.458 --> 18:17.750
Please join me in giving a warm
welcome to Miss Terdie.

18:17.792 --> 18:20.291
-Ter-die
-[Callaghan]: Miss Terdie,
I beg your pardon.

18:20.333 --> 18:23.125
Please join me in welcoming
[Sounds like]: Mr. D.

18:23.166 --> 18:26.250
-[Clapping]
-What? I'm Mr. D.

18:26.291 --> 18:28.875
-[Clapping]
-[Gerry]: You gotta be
kidding me.

18:28.917 --> 18:31.125
-Can you believe that?
Another Mr. D.

18:31.166 --> 18:33.458
-It's not Mr. D, she's
Miss Terdie.
-Mr. D. I know.

18:33.500 --> 18:35.750
-Miss Terdie.
-Mr. D. It's incredible.

18:35.792 --> 18:37.959
-Miss Terdie.
-[Miss Terdie]: Thank you.

18:38.000 --> 18:41.417
I'm very excited to be joining
the staff at Xavier Academy.

18:41.458 --> 18:46.083
And I'm looking forward to
seeing you all between the
covers.

18:46.125 --> 18:49.041
Of the books. At the library.

18:49.083 --> 18:51.291
-She seems nice.

18:51.333 --> 18:53.583
[All clap]
-Okay.

18:53.625 --> 18:55.875
-Thank you Miss Terdie.

18:55.917 --> 18:58.875
Alright, let's get out there.
Study hard.

18:58.917 --> 19:01.250
Dismissed.

19:01.291 --> 19:03.709
-I like your hair Miss Mason.
It's so fun.

19:03.750 --> 19:07.375
-Oh thank you.
Just trying something different.

19:08.458 --> 19:10.417
Oh my god.

19:11.625 --> 19:14.291
-[Miss Terdie]: Ohh.
-Well, look at this.
This is a little...

19:14.333 --> 19:16.625
-Ouch.
-Yeah. Well, got in a fight.

19:16.667 --> 19:20.166
Anyway, I'm sure this is a bit
uncomfortable for you more.

19:20.208 --> 19:25.208
But I just wanted you to know
that I'm not going to bring up
what you said to me last night.

19:25.250 --> 19:27.458
-What did I say to
you last night?

19:27.500 --> 19:30.000
-You tried to get me to come
home with you and your husband
at the bar.

19:30.041 --> 19:32.208
What do you mean,
what did you say?

19:32.250 --> 19:35.667
-I have no idea...
What your talking about.

19:35.709 --> 19:39.291
-Hey, secrets.
I'm fine with that.

19:39.333 --> 19:45.041
Speaking of secrets. You should
know, I'm Mr. Duncan but the
kids call me Mr. D.

19:45.083 --> 19:48.458
So maybe they could just call
you Emma, 'cause you're not
really a teacher anyway.

19:48.500 --> 19:52.250
-Well, my name is Miss Terdie.
-We both can't be Mr. D.

19:52.291 --> 19:56.250
-My name is Miss Terdie.
It's not shortened.
There is no short form.

19:56.291 --> 19:58.500
It's the whole thing.
-Why not go with Miss Terdie?

19:58.542 --> 20:00.875
-My name is Miss Terdie.
-I'm Mr. D.

20:00.917 --> 20:03.166
-I'm Miss Terdie, the boss
of the library, okay?

20:03.208 --> 20:06.000
-Miss Terd.
-I'm excited to work with you.

20:07.667 --> 20:10.375
